workflow Refund Resolver
runner codex

agent intake
title Intake request
prompt Read the request in examples/refund-request.md. Summarize the requested action and the concrete identifiers needed by downstream agents. Do not modify files.
after none

agent route
title Classify and route
prompt Inspect examples/refund-request.md. Classify the request, state which independent checks are required, and return a compact routing decision for downstream agents. Do not modify files.
after intake

agent policy
title Policy lookup
prompt Read examples/refund-request.md and policies/refunds.md. Decide whether the request is eligible under the written policy. Cite the exact rule and return a concise decision. Do not modify files.
after route

agent history
title Account history
prompt Read examples/refund-request.md and examples/transactions.csv. Determine whether the charges are duplicates. Explain the evidence and return a concise decision. Do not modify files.
after route

agent compose
title Draft resolution
prompt Read examples/refund-request.md, policies/refunds.md, and examples/transactions.csv. Compose the final refund decision and a customer-facing response. Do not modify files.
after policy, history

approval review
title Human approval
after compose

agent payout
title Issue refund
prompt The human approved the workflow. Read the request and supporting files, then produce a final execution record describing the refund that should be issued. Do not perform an external payment and do not modify files.
after review
